GLOBAL
Standard arms: swords (short/long/two-handed), axes, maces, spears, bows,
daggers; quality varies by maker's mark and metal source
Iron vs steel: iron is common/cheap; steel holds edge longer, brighter
color, lighter weight for same size, cleaner ring when struck
Armor grades: leather (flexible, quiet), chainmail (weight/protection
tradeoff), plate (expensive, restricts movement, requires fitting)
Enchanted weapons: glow faintly, unnaturally warm, or lighter than expected;
Violet Compact registered dangerous enchanted items — registry exploited;
many registered items changed hands under duress
Buying used: ask for proof of ownership; stolen goods create legal liability
at city gates; guards check against known stolen-arms lists
Repair: nicks are normal; cracks near the hilt or warped blades are
dangerous; a smith can assess in minutes
Arrows/bolts: stockpile before wilderness travel; broadheads for game,
war-points for armor penetration; field-made arrows fly poorly
~

MIDGAARD
Guild Concordat licenses all smiths; unlicensed forges exist in outer wards
but work is unguaranteed; ask for the Concordat stamp
Upland ore quality varies by shipment; current prices elevated while
northern routes are disrupted
Road wardens purchase arms in bulk through Guard Command contracts; civilian
pricing is higher but quality is consistent
~
KOWLOON
Wardens of Iron bulk-purchase militia arms through city contracts; civilian
grade is available but priced accordingly
Thaumaturgic exchange in the eastern corridor: enchantment residue assessed,
spent components recycled, reagents sold; Temple Circle monitors it
Maritime imports via Tide Gate bring steel from Kiess and Midgaard forges;
blue-sash inspectors verify proof of ownership on all declared weapons
Night market (violet-marked) deals in arms with sparse provenance; legally
grey but not suppressed — know what you are buying
~
KIESS
Wall Command purchases standard kit through Roc Road trade contracts; militia
supply is reliable; civilian availability varies by recent caravan arrivals
Roc Road brings eastern steel from Midgaard forges; salvage parties also
recover weapons and components from Evermeet ruins and Conclave-adjacent sites
Serathi do not use standard boots; talon-clasp guards and wrapped talon-braces
fill the HOOVES equipment slot; smiths in the Roc Road district stock them
Sage's Alcove warns against carrying recovered crystal shards near weapons or
sleeping near them — residual Conclave enchantment; treat as hazardous
~
RAKUEN
Ember Wardens maintain a centralized arms depot; civilian purchases require
basic Ledger registration during declared emergencies
Salvage court can requisition weapons and tools for disaster-response labor
during active emergency declarations — contested but legally valid
Arms from Midgaard via Eccentric Woodland routes have high markup from
Woodland path-guide charges; locally-made tools are cheaper
Quality is practical rather than polished — a frontier city under continuous
reconstruction, not a garrison on campaign footing
~
MAFDET
Exotic arms arrive via Saltglass Reach: eastern desert bronze, pyramid-site
copper alloys, sea-ivory hilts
Quarantine Ledger may flag unusual weapons from pyramid excavations; some
have ritual properties that complicate resale
Sand-Sea Carters' Guild transport contracts include arms; caravan-grade arms
inspected at Tide Gate before sale
~
